{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1484,"text":"Where does the end begin?"},{"time":3440,"text":"Well, for me, it all began\nwith this little fellow."},{"time":8240,"text":"This adorable organism --"},{"time":9680,"text":"well, I think it's adorable --"},{"time":11160,"text":"is called Tetrahymena\nand it's a single-celled creature."},{"time":15200,"text":"It's also been known as pond scum."},{"time":17120,"text":"So that's right, my career\nstarted with pond scum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21680,"text":"Now, it was no surprise\nI became a scientist."},{"time":24760,"text":"Growing up far away from here,"},{"time":26880,"text":"as a little girl I was deadly curious"},{"time":29800,"text":"about everything alive."},{"time":31800,"text":"I used to pick up lethally poisonous\nstinging jellyfish and sing to them."},{"time":37800,"text":"And so starting my career,"},{"time":40640,"text":"I was deadly curious\nabout fundamental mysteries"},{"time":44040,"text":"of the most basic building blocks of life,"},{"time":47400,"text":"and I was fortunate to live in a society\nwhere that curiosity was valued."}]},{"cues":[{"time":53120,"text":"Now, for me, this little\npond scum critter Tetrahymena"},{"time":55720,"text":"was a great way to study\nthe fundamental mystery"},{"time":58040,"text":"I was most curious about:"},{"time":60120,"text":"those bundles of DNA\nin our cells called chromosomes."},{"time":64519,"text":"And it was because I was curious\nabout the very ends of chromosomes,"},{"time":70960,"text":"known as telomeres."},{"time":73000,"text":"Now, when I started my quest,"},{"time":75720,"text":"all we knew was that they helped\nprotect the ends of chromosomes."},{"time":79640,"text":"It was important when cells divide."},{"time":81360,"text":"It was really important,"},{"time":82760,"text":"but I wanted to find out\nwhat telomeres consisted of,"},{"time":86880,"text":"and for that, I needed a lot of them."},{"time":89680,"text":"And it so happens\nthat cute little Tetrahymena"},{"time":92280,"text":"has a lot of short linear chromosomes,"},{"time":95320,"text":"around 20,000,"},{"time":96960,"text":"so lots of telomeres."},{"time":99200,"text":"And I discovered that telomeres\nconsisted of special segments"},{"time":103920,"text":"of noncoding DNA right\nat the very ends of chromosomes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107640,"text":"But here's a problem."},{"time":109840,"text":"Now, we all start life as a single cell."},{"time":112680,"text":"It multiples to two.\nTwo becomes four. Four becomes eight,"},{"time":115440,"text":"and on and on to form\nthe 200 million billion cells"},{"time":118680,"text":"that make up our adult body."},{"time":120960,"text":"And some of those cells\nhave to divide thousands of times."},{"time":125640,"text":"In fact, even as I stand here before you,"},{"time":128520,"text":"all throughout my body,\ncells are furiously replenishing"},{"time":131640,"text":"to, well, keep me\nstanding here before you."},{"time":135040,"text":"So every time a cell divides,\nall of its DNA has to be copied,"},{"time":139520,"text":"all of the coding DNA\ninside of those chromosomes,"},{"time":142160,"text":"because that carries\nthe vital operating instructions"},{"time":146720,"text":"that keep our cells in good working order,"},{"time":149760,"text":"so my heart cells can keep a steady beat,"},{"time":154440,"text":"which I assure you\nthey're not doing right now,"},{"time":156680,"text":"and my immune cells"},{"time":159600,"text":"can fight off bacteria and viruses,"},{"time":164520,"text":"and our brain cells\ncan save the memory of our first kiss"},{"time":169400,"text":"and keep on learning throughout life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":172520,"text":"But there is a glitch\nin the way DNA is copied."},{"time":177360,"text":"It is just one of those facts of life."},{"time":180240,"text":"Every time the cell divides\nand the DNA is copied,"},{"time":183640,"text":"some of that DNA from the ends\ngets worn down and shortened,"},{"time":187680,"text":"some of that telomere DNA."},{"time":190000,"text":"And think about it"},{"time":192200,"text":"like the protective caps\nat the ends of your shoelace."},{"time":195680,"text":"And those keep the shoelace,\nor the chromosome, from fraying,"},{"time":201240,"text":"and when that tip\ngets too short, it falls off,"},{"time":206600,"text":"and that worn down telomere\nsends a signal to the cells."},{"time":211520,"text":"\"The DNA is no longer being protected.\""},{"time":213560,"text":"It sends a signal. Time to die."},{"time":215600,"text":"So, end of story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217080,"text":"Well, sorry, not so fast."},{"time":221120,"text":"It can't be the end of the story,"},{"time":222760,"text":"because life hasn't died\noff the face of the earth."},{"time":225280,"text":"So I was curious:"},{"time":227920,"text":"if such wear and tear is inevitable,"},{"time":230040,"text":"how on earth does Mother Nature make sure"},{"time":233280,"text":"we can keep our chromosomes intact?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":236600,"text":"Now, remember that little\npond scum critter Tetrahymena?"},{"time":241080,"text":"The craziest thing was,\nTetrahymena cells never got old and died."},{"time":246600,"text":"Their telomeres weren't shortening\nas time marched on."},{"time":253320,"text":"Sometimes they even got longer."},{"time":255120,"text":"Something else was at work,"},{"time":257040,"text":"and believe me, that something\nwas not in any textbook."},{"time":260680,"text":"So working in my lab with\nmy extraordinary student Carol Greider --"},{"time":263960,"text":"and Carol and I shared\nthe Nobel Prize for this work --"},{"time":267400,"text":"we began running experiments"},{"time":270200,"text":"and we discovered\ncells do have something else."},{"time":273960,"text":"It was a previously undreamed-of enzyme"},{"time":276960,"text":"that could replenish,\nmake longer, telomeres,"},{"time":280520,"text":"and we named it telomerase."},{"time":283840,"text":"And when we removed\nour pond scum's telomerase,"},{"time":287480,"text":"their telomeres ran down and they died."},{"time":290600,"text":"So it was thanks\nto their plentiful telomerase"},{"time":293320,"text":"that our pond scum critters never got old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":298040,"text":"OK, now, that's\nan incredibly hopeful message"},{"time":302080,"text":"for us humans to be\nreceiving from pond scum,"},{"time":306400,"text":"because it turns out"},{"time":307680,"text":"that as we humans age,\nour telomeres do shorten,"},{"time":311520,"text":"and remarkably,\nthat shortening is aging us."},{"time":315560,"text":"Generally speaking,\nthe longer your telomeres,"},{"time":317760,"text":"the better off you are."},{"time":320640,"text":"It's the overshortening of telomeres"},{"time":322400,"text":"that leads us to feel and see\nsigns of aging."},{"time":326480,"text":"My skin cells start to die"},{"time":328320,"text":"and I start to see fine lines, wrinkles."},{"time":331200,"text":"Hair pigment cells die."},{"time":333480,"text":"You start to see gray."},{"time":335480,"text":"Immune system cells die."},{"time":338160,"text":"You increase your risks of getting sick."},{"time":340880,"text":"In fact, the cumulative research\nfrom the last 20 years"},{"time":344520,"text":"has made clear that telomere attrition"},{"time":347720,"text":"is contributing to our risks\nof getting cardiovascular diseases,"},{"time":352280,"text":"Alzheimer's, some cancers and diabetes,"},{"time":356120,"text":"the very conditions many of us die of."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360600,"text":"And so we have to think about this."},{"time":365360,"text":"What is going on?"},{"time":367320,"text":"This attrition,"},{"time":369080,"text":"we look and we feel older, yeah."},{"time":371080,"text":"Our telomeres are losing\nthe war of attrition faster."},{"time":374640,"text":"And those of us who feel youthful longer,"},{"time":378120,"text":"it turns out our telomeres\nare staying longer"},{"time":380800,"text":"for longer periods of time,"},{"time":382120,"text":"extending our feelings of youthfulness"},{"time":384920,"text":"and reducing the risks\nof all we most dread"},{"time":388440,"text":"as the birthdays go by."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392480,"text":"OK,"},{"time":393720,"text":"seems like a no-brainer."},{"time":396640,"text":"Now, if my telomeres are connected"},{"time":400320,"text":"to how quickly\nI'm going to feel and get old,"},{"time":403920,"text":"if my telomeres can be\nrenewed by my telomerase,"},{"time":408400,"text":"then all I have to do to reverse\nthe signs and symptoms of aging"},{"time":412920,"text":"is figure out where to buy\nthat Costco-sized bottle"},{"time":416480,"text":"of grade A organic\nfair trade telomerase, right?"},{"time":420680,"text":"Great! Problem solved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":422360,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":423400,"text":"Not so fast, I'm sorry."},{"time":426320,"text":"Alas, that's not the case."},{"time":429800,"text":"OK. And why?"},{"time":431080,"text":"It's because human genetics has taught us"},{"time":435440,"text":"that when it comes to our telomerase,"},{"time":438560,"text":"we humans live on a knife edge."},{"time":442000,"text":"OK, simply put,"},{"time":444280,"text":"yes, nudging up telomerase\ndoes decrease the risks of some diseases,"},{"time":450560,"text":"but it also increases the risks\nof certain and rather nasty cancers."},{"time":456640,"text":"So even if you could buy\nthat Costco-sized bottle of telomerase,"},{"time":462440,"text":"and there are many websites\nmarketing such dubious products,"},{"time":469200,"text":"the problem is you could\nnudge up your risks of cancers."},{"time":474600,"text":"And we don't want that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477400,"text":"Now, don't worry,"},{"time":480160,"text":"and because, while I think\nit's kind of funny that right now,"},{"time":485080,"text":"you know, many of us may be thinking,\nwell, I'd rather be like pond scum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490720,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":494640,"text":"There is something for us humans"},{"time":496240,"text":"in the story of telomeres\nand their maintenance."},{"time":498840,"text":"But I want to get one thing clear."},{"time":500520,"text":"It isn't about enormously\nextending human lifespan"},{"time":503720,"text":"or immortality."},{"time":505760,"text":"It's about health span."},{"time":508680,"text":"Now, health span is the number\nof years of your life"},{"time":511400,"text":"when you're free of disease,\nyou're healthy, you're productive,"},{"time":515200,"text":"you're zestfully enjoying life."},{"time":517360,"text":"Disease span, the opposite of health span,"},{"time":520080,"text":"is the time of your life\nspent feeling old and sick and dying."},{"time":523840,"text":"So the real question becomes,"},{"time":527440,"text":"OK, if I can't guzzle telomerase,"},{"time":530920,"text":"do I have control\nover my telomeres' length"},{"time":534120,"text":"and hence my well-being, my health,"},{"time":537880,"text":"without those downsides of cancer risks?"},{"time":541480,"text":"OK?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":542840,"text":"So, it's the year 2000."},{"time":545600,"text":"Now, I've been minutely scrutinizing\nlittle teeny tiny telomeres"},{"time":550840,"text":"very happily for many years,"},{"time":553280,"text":"when into my lab walks\na psychologist named Elissa Epel."},{"time":557120,"text":"Now, Elissa's expertise is in the effects\nof severe, chronic psychological stress"},{"time":563840,"text":"on our mind's and our body's health."},{"time":567280,"text":"And there she was standing in my lab,"},{"time":569240,"text":"which ironically overlooked\nthe entrance to a mortuary, and --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":574320,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":576680,"text":"And she had a life-and-death\nquestion for me."},{"time":579360,"text":"\"What happens to telomeres\nin people who are chronically stressed?\""},{"time":583040,"text":"she asked me."},{"time":584280,"text":"You see, she'd been studying caregivers,"},{"time":586440,"text":"and specifically mothers of children\nwith a chronic condition,"},{"time":592000,"text":"be it gut disorder,\nbe it autism, you name it --"},{"time":596560,"text":"a group obviously under enormous\nand prolonged psychological stress."},{"time":604600,"text":"I have to say, her question"},{"time":607080,"text":"changed me profoundly."},{"time":609120,"text":"See, all this time\nI had been thinking of telomeres"},{"time":611880,"text":"as those miniscule\nmolecular structures that they are,"},{"time":615200,"text":"and the genes that control telomeres."},{"time":618760,"text":"And when Elissa asked me\nabout studying caregivers,"},{"time":621960,"text":"I suddenly saw telomeres\nin a whole new light."},{"time":627560,"text":"I saw beyond the genes and the chromosomes"},{"time":630320,"text":"into the lives of the real people\nwe were studying."},{"time":634280,"text":"And I'm a mom myself,"},{"time":636520,"text":"and at that moment,"},{"time":638480,"text":"I was struck by the image of these women"},{"time":642320,"text":"dealing with a child with a condition"},{"time":646320,"text":"very difficult to deal with,\noften without help."},{"time":650080,"text":"And such women, simply,"},{"time":653120,"text":"often look worn down."},{"time":657680,"text":"So was it possible their telomeres\nwere worn down as well?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":661720,"text":"So our collective curiosity\nwent into overdrive."},{"time":665400,"text":"Elissa selected for our first study\na group of such caregiving mothers,"},{"time":669320,"text":"and we wanted to ask:\nWhat's the length of their telomeres"},{"time":673520,"text":"compared with the number of years\nthat they have been caregiving"},{"time":678120,"text":"for their child with a chronic condition?"},{"time":680920,"text":"So four years go by"},{"time":683720,"text":"and the day comes\nwhen all the results are in,"},{"time":686880,"text":"and Elissa looked down\nat our first scatterplot"},{"time":689600,"text":"and literally gasped,"},{"time":692960,"text":"because there was a pattern to the data,"},{"time":695600,"text":"and it was the exact gradient\nthat we most feared might exist."},{"time":701040,"text":"It was right there on the page."},{"time":703000,"text":"The longer, the more years that is,"},{"time":705440,"text":"the mother had been\nin this caregiving situation,"},{"time":708360,"text":"no matter her age,"},{"time":710080,"text":"the shorter were her telomeres."},{"time":712080,"text":"And the more she perceived"},{"time":715200,"text":"her situation as being more stressful,"},{"time":719880,"text":"the lower was her telomerase\nand the shorter were her telomeres."}]},{"cues":[{"time":727360,"text":"So we had discovered something unheard of:"},{"time":730880,"text":"the more chronic stress you are under,\nthe shorter your telomeres,"},{"time":734760,"text":"meaning the more likely you were\nto fall victim to an early disease span"},{"time":740440,"text":"and perhaps untimely death."},{"time":743000,"text":"Our findings meant\nthat people's life events"},{"time":747360,"text":"and the way we respond to these events"},{"time":750320,"text":"can change how you\nmaintain your telomeres."},{"time":756080,"text":"So telomere length wasn't\njust a matter of age counted in years."},{"time":762520,"text":"Elissa's question to me,"},{"time":763960,"text":"back when she first came to my lab,\nindeed had been a life-and-death question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769920,"text":"Now, luckily, hidden\nin that data there was hope."},{"time":774080,"text":"We noticed that some mothers,"},{"time":775720,"text":"despite having been carefully caring\nfor their children for many years,"},{"time":779880,"text":"had been able to maintain their telomeres."},{"time":783520,"text":"So studying these women closely revealed\nthat they were resilient to stress."},{"time":788960,"text":"Somehow they were able\nto experience their circumstances"},{"time":791640,"text":"not as a threat day in and day out"},{"time":794160,"text":"but as a challenge,"},{"time":795840,"text":"and this has led to a very important\ninsight for all of us:"},{"time":799920,"text":"we have control over the way we age"},{"time":803720,"text":"all the way down into our cells."}]},{"cues":[{"time":807680,"text":"OK, now our initial curiosity\nbecame infectious."},{"time":811120,"text":"Thousands of scientists\nfrom different fields"},{"time":813720,"text":"added their expertise\nto telomere research,"},{"time":817240,"text":"and the findings have poured in."},{"time":819840,"text":"It's up to over 10,000\nscientific papers and counting."},{"time":826840,"text":"So several studies\nrapidly confirmed our initial finding"},{"time":830360,"text":"that yes, chronic stress\nis bad for telomeres."},{"time":834720,"text":"And now many are revealing"},{"time":836120,"text":"that we have more control\nover this particular aging process"},{"time":840040,"text":"than any of us could ever have imagined."},{"time":842880,"text":"A few examples:"},{"time":844120,"text":"a study from the University\nof California, Los Angeles"},{"time":848280,"text":"of people who are caring\nfor a relative with dementia, long-term,"},{"time":853720,"text":"and looked at their caregiver's\ntelomere maintenance capacity"},{"time":859200,"text":"and found that it was improved"},{"time":861440,"text":"by them practicing a form of meditation"},{"time":865280,"text":"for as little as 12 minutes\na day for two months."},{"time":869720,"text":"Attitude matters."},{"time":871400,"text":"If you're habitually a negative thinker,"},{"time":873800,"text":"you typically see a stressful situation\nwith a threat stress response,"},{"time":879560,"text":"meaning if your boss wants to see you,"},{"time":882040,"text":"you automatically think,\n\"I'm about to be fired,\""},{"time":884400,"text":"and your blood vessels constrict,"},{"time":886000,"text":"and your level of the stress\nhormone cortisol creeps up,"},{"time":890360,"text":"and then it stays up,"},{"time":891920,"text":"and over time, that persistently\nhigh level of the cortisol"},{"time":896880,"text":"actually damps down your telomerase."},{"time":898800,"text":"Not good for your telomeres."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902200,"text":"On the other hand,"},{"time":903480,"text":"if you typically see something stressful\nas a challenge to be tackled,"},{"time":909480,"text":"then blood flows to your heart\nand to your brain,"},{"time":912960,"text":"and you experience a brief\nbut energizing spike of cortisol."},{"time":917680,"text":"And thanks to that habitual\n\"bring it on\" attitude,"},{"time":920240,"text":"your telomeres do just fine."},{"time":925600,"text":"So ..."},{"time":928160,"text":"What is all of this telling us?"},{"time":933480,"text":"Your telomeres do just fine."},{"time":935440,"text":"You really do have power\nto change what is happening"},{"time":941440,"text":"to your own telomeres."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944480,"text":"But our curiosity\njust got more and more intense,"},{"time":950520,"text":"because we started to wonder,"},{"time":952960,"text":"what about factors outside our own skin?"},{"time":956200,"text":"Could they impact\nour telomere maintenance as well?"},{"time":960800,"text":"You know, we humans\nare intensely social beings."},{"time":964160,"text":"Was it even possible\nthat our telomeres were social as well?"},{"time":969440,"text":"And the results have been startling."},{"time":972400,"text":"As early as childhood,"},{"time":976360,"text":"emotional neglect, exposure to violence,"},{"time":979560,"text":"bullying and racism"},{"time":981600,"text":"all impact your telomeres,\nand the effects are long-term."},{"time":987800,"text":"Can you imagine the impact on children"},{"time":990120,"text":"of living years in a war zone?"},{"time":994240,"text":"People who can't trust their neighbors"},{"time":996120,"text":"and who don't feel safe\nin their neighborhoods"},{"time":999280,"text":"consistently have shorter telomeres."},{"time":1002600,"text":"So your home address\nmatters for telomeres as well."},{"time":1005600,"text":"On the flip side,"},{"time":1008200,"text":"tight-knit communities,\nbeing in a marriage long-term,"},{"time":1011520,"text":"and lifelong friendships, even,"},{"time":1014480,"text":"all improve telomere maintenance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018360,"text":"So what is all this telling us?"},{"time":1021840,"text":"It's telling us that I have the power\nto impact my own telomeres,"},{"time":1026359,"text":"and I also have the power to impact yours."},{"time":1029680,"text":"Telomere science has told us\njust how interconnected we all are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1037520,"text":"But I'm still curious."},{"time":1039920,"text":"I do wonder"},{"time":1043200,"text":"what legacy all of us"},{"time":1046560,"text":"will leave for the next generation?"},{"time":1048960,"text":"Will we invest"},{"time":1050560,"text":"in the next young woman or man"},{"time":1053600,"text":"peering through a microscope\nat the next little critter,"},{"time":1057840,"text":"the next bit of pond scum,"},{"time":1060520,"text":"curious about a question\nwe don't even know today is a question?"},{"time":1064320,"text":"It could be a great question\nthat could impact all the world."},{"time":1067240,"text":"And maybe, maybe you're curious about you."},{"time":1072080,"text":"Now that you know\nhow to protect your telomeres,"},{"time":1074360,"text":"are you curious what are you going to do"},{"time":1076289,"text":"with all those decades\nof brimming good health?"},{"time":1079200,"text":"And now that you know you could impact\nthe telomeres of others,"},{"time":1084040,"text":"are you curious"},{"time":1086040,"text":"how will you make a difference?"},{"time":1089880,"text":"And now that you know the power\nof curiosity to change the world,"},{"time":1094000,"text":"how will you make sure\nthat the world invests in curiosity"},{"time":1100240,"text":"for the sake of the generations\nthat will come after us?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1106560,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107800,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}